In the seminars the different methods of analysing the Biblical texts are studied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course describes different contemporary methods of the Biblical hermeneutics and the relations between different approaches.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. The student is sytematically acquainted with the contemporary methods of Biblical hermeneutics and can describe their possibilities and limits. The student is able to show how the plurality of meanings of the Biblical texts is related to the interpretive methods used to understand them. 2. Student analyses the assigned authors' texts; can outline the content of the texts; can relate texts and contexts; evaluates the reading material and justifies in argumented way his/her evaluation.
